McGee Creek first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that McGee Creek had a population of 45. The population density was {{convert|11.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of McGee Creek was 30 (67%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 2 (4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (2%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 4 (9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 8 (18%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 6 persons (13%).

There were 25 housing units at an average density of {{convert|6.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 15 (60%) were occupied. Of these, 11 (73%) were owner-occupied, and 4 (27%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=McGee Creek CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0644830 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 28, 2025}}</ref>

